  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mali: Access to Justice Pilot Program in Mopti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To empower victims of crime in the region of Mopti to access justice and obtain tangible 
and fair results from the perception of users through the courts and, in appropriate cases, 
through inter-communal and other informal justice mechanisms, depending on the nature 
and seriousness of the grievance at stake. 2) To raise awareness of the traditional leaders, communities and the general public of the 
applicable legal framework and international standards as well as their ability to apply the 
knowledge in practice through their involvement in dispute resolution mechanisms as providers and users. 3) To support the Mopti First Instance and Appeal Criminal Courts redressing criminal law violations in 
compliance with applicable domestic laws and international standards with tangible results 
that are enforced in a timely manner to the satisfaction of the local population.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: The Ministry of Justice (MOJ) and Malian formal and informal justice sector. Indirect beneficiaries: Malian citizens.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to address the population&apos;s needs to access lawful and effective dispute resolution mechanisms to solve criminal law related disputes in central Mali.</narrative>
  </description>
